      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-advanced-authoring"
        },
        "markdown": "## Advanced path\n\n1. If you still need the primitive model for bridge, field, or script, use **Advanced Primitives**.\n2. If you want to formalize relationships, use **Edge Class Authoring**.\n3. If you need to import or expose reusable authority across boundaries, use **Bridge Authoring**.\n4. If behavior needs to live visibly in the graph, use **Script Authoring**.\n5. Treat node classes as the umbrella idea: advanced authoring is about making structure reusable and inspectable.\n\nAdvanced work is usually about explicit reuse, authority, or behavior."
      }
    },
